	<!-- In LAMS 2.3 there was a change in this section in all tools and core 
		parts (central, learning, monitoring etc.) All LAMS web application now use 
		shared application context. See refBeanContext.xml file in lams_common for 
		its description. This refBeanContext.xml contains definition of the shared 
		context. It is located by this entry: <context-param> <param-name>locatorFactorySelector</param-name> 
		<param-value>classpath:/org/lamsfoundation/lams/beanRefContext.xml</param-value> 
		</context-param> telling to look for refBeanContext.xml files in selected 
		part of the classpath. Currently LAMS has only one refBeanContext.xml with 
		one shared context definition. Lams_central uses only beans from the shared 
		context "context.central". That is why there is no value in contextConfigLocation. 
		Even so, this parameter needs to be declared with empty value for locatorFactorySelector 
		to work properly. Also, if no local application context file is declare, 
		there MUST be a file named "applicationContext.xml" in web/WEB-INF containing 
		empty bean list, otherwise there will be errors during start up. If there 
		are local (private for web application; see tools and admin for example) 
		bean definitions, path to application context XML file can still be added 
		to contextConfigLocation. -->

